    <item>
      <title>Career Reflection: building digital license plates for drones at 24</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/initial-commit/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/initial-commit/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;career-reflection-building-digital-license-plates-for-drones-at-24&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Career Reflection: building digital license plates for drones at 24&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#career-reflection-building-digital-license-plates-for-drones-at-24&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In 2022, I took on a project that would define much of my year: building &lt;strong&gt;Remote ID&lt;/strong&gt; for our drones. For those unfamiliar, Remote ID is the FAA’s new requirement—basically a digital license plate that broadcasts a drone’s identity and location in real-time. Without it, our entire fleet would be grounded. No pressure.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title> How a Classroom in Vietnam Changed My Life</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/from-300k-to-0/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 10 Aug 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/from-300k-to-0/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;how-a-classroom-in-vietnam-changed-my-life&#34;&gt;&#xA;  How a Classroom in Vietnam Changed My Life&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#how-a-classroom-in-vietnam-changed-my-life&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;div style=&#34;display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1.5em; margin: 2em 0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;figure style=&#34;flex: 1 1 200px; text-align: center;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/vh-first-class.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Vietnam Hearts Classroom&#34; style=&#34;width:100%; max-width:250px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-first-day-i-almost-quit&#34;&gt;&#xA;  The First Day I Almost Quit&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#the-first-day-i-almost-quit&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When I first walked into that classroom in Vietnam, I barely knew a word of Vietnamese and had never taught before. My first lesson was a disaster—kids talking over me, no one paying attention, and me not understanding a thing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
